data.title: An Authentic History of Lancaster County Part 2
data.meta_description: An Authentic History of Lancaster County Part 2 - Free ebook download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read book online for free. This document contains correspondence related to land transactions in Lancaster County, Pennsylvania in 1779-1780. It includes a letter from William Henry informing President Reed about John Musser purchasing 500 acres of land known as the Conestoga Manor from John Penn, as well as correspondence between Reed and Judge Atlee regarding investigating the land deal. It also describes Charles Hall seizing the tract of land known as the Indian Town in 1780, and John Musser confronting Hall with an abstract from the original deed showing the land was conveyed to John Penn.
